cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM 

This paper deals with the Constraint Satisfaction Problem (CSP) and the parameterized complexity of modal satisfiability. The subject matter is closely related to logic and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of treewidth and graph theory also suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are relevant sub-categories. Finally, the investigation of parameterized complexity suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) may also be a relevant sub-category.
